description: Capmatinib and crizotinib are small molecule inhibitors of MET that are FDA-approved and/or NCCN-listed for adult patients with metastatic non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC) harboring MET alterations. Across multiple case reports, the MET Y1230H mutation was detected in four patients with MET exon 14-positive (D1010H) NSCLC after progression on crizotinib treatment and in one patient after progression on capmatinib (PMID: 27666659, 29128427, 28522754, 28396313, 27987579).

Capmatinib and crizotinib are small molecule inhibitors of MET that are FDA-approved and/or NCCN-listed for adult patients with metastatic non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC) harboring MET alterations.
